    "The results of the four experimental sets (Q1-Q4), the technical explanation of LLMs, and Dewey's moral philosophy all support the conclusion that experience plays a fundamental and substantial role in the formation of moral competence.",
    "RLHF serves as the key driving force in moral competence development by distributing rewards and penalties.",
    "This implies that a moral machine can be realized through an empiricist approach, without strictly adhering to either the AGI or ANI approach.",
    "Specifically, without pretrained data (moral experience), LLMs would not generate the habits and instincts underpinning moral practice.",
    "Without RLHF, LLMs would not converge with human moral norms nor achieve AI alignment."
